{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down acceptance-criteria completeness and verifiability with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"acceptance-criteria completeness and verifiability"},{"coaching":"Run a quick pre-mortem on experiment failure modes and resolution path: how could this plan fail?","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f9e7c8e55b79df027"],"move_id":"3","move_name":"pre-mortem","subject":"experiment failure modes and resolution path"},{"coaching":"Plan how positive-fixture LLM fidelity verification approach will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f01007ca81508fa44"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"positive-fixture LLM fidelity verification approach"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":1,"blocking":0,"dropped":6,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":12,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":4,"ran":true,"references":4,"resolved":1,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":3},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":12,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":8713,"file_impact":5,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":12,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":52,"verify_lint_abstained":52},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":2194,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":5,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["E5","T8"],"floored_finding_ids":["f9e7c8e55b79df027","f01007ca81508fa44"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":204.0,"llm_calls":27,"llm_ms":444706.0,"total_ms":445004.9,"verify_requests":26},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["1 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable).","vague/subjective terms present: properly"],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] State the required fields (and their expected values) for a `criteria_routing.json` entry in the plan, or explicitly say 'follow the schema of an existing entry in that file' so the agent has a deterministic default.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan says 'Add one activated project plan-review criterion, `project.portability`, through `.rebar/criteria_routing.json`' without specifying required fields (e.g., criterion id key, scope field, pass field, enabled flag).","Move entry fields are fully enumerated: 'id: project-portability, name: restore rebar portability, applies_when: [\"project.portability\"], template: ...' — routing entry receives no equivalent enumeration.","ABSENCE: No example or field list for criteria_routing.json entry schema appears anywhere in the plan."],"finding":"The plan instructs the agent to activate `project.portability` 'through `.rebar/criteria_routing.json`' but does not state the JSON schema or field names for a new criterion entry in that file. The move entry schema is fully specified (id/name/applies_when/template), but the routing-file entry format is left implicit. An agent unfamiliar with the existing file must infer the structure by reading the current file contents — a defaultable gap, but one that could produce a silently malformed entry if the existing schema is non-obvious.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f115e326339ef16be","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — '.rebar/criteria_routing.json' bullet; AC 1 (criterion_activation)","norm_id":"n4dd8e5dee3bec8ab","priority":0.066,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An agent creates a routing entry with a wrong field name (e.g., 'criterion' instead of 'id', or 'scopes' instead of 'scope') that the loader silently ignores, leaving the criterion inactive while AC 1 (criterion_activation) tests pass against a mocked registry."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a one-line note such as: 'The routing entry must include the same fields as existing entries (e.g., `criterion_id`, `scopes: [\"leaf\", \"container\"]`, `pass: 1`, `enabled: true`); copy the nearest existing entry as a template.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Confirm that the docs/plan-review-gate.md dogfood documentation for the project-portability move does NOT add rows to the existing move-table parsed by test_move_registry_matches_docs_table (or update that test to exclude project-sourced moves).","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'Document the committed rebar configuration as the client-facing dogfood example'","test_plan_review.py:605-618: test_move_registry_matches_docs_table asserts `set(rows) == set(reg)` where `reg` is `orchestrator.MOVE_REGISTRY` (the built-in registry, not project extensions)","The project move is loaded via load_move_registry() which merges .rebar/plan_review_moves.json but MOVE_REGISTRY itself is never mutated","The plan does not name test_move_registry_matches_docs_table as a consumer requiring attention or exclusion from the documentation scope"],"finding":"The plan's documentation step (AC-12, 'Document the committed rebar configuration as the client-facing dogfood example' in docs/plan-review-gate.md) may collide with the existing test test_move_registry_matches_docs_table in tests/unit/test_plan_review.py, which asserts the plan-review-gate.md move table matches MOVE_REGISTRY id-for-id. If the documentation adds the project-portability move entry to that table, this test fails because the project move lives in .rebar/plan_review_moves.json, not MOVE_REGISTRY.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f93ecf304d70a993b","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Success Criteria / AC-12 (`docs/plan-review-gate.md` documentation) and tests/unit/test_plan_review.py:test_move_registry_matches_docs_table (line 605-618)","norm_id":"n881e001788377c5d","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["If docs/plan-review-gate.md's dogfood section adds a move table row for 'project-portability', test_move_registry_matches_docs_table's regex parser picks it up, finds it missing from MOVE_REGISTRY, and the assertion `set(rows) == set(reg)` fails with a spurious test break.","Alternatively if the documentation section is kept outside the move table (e.g. in a new subsection), no conflict arises — but the plan does not specify this."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add the project move documentation in a new subsection (e.g. '### Project-supplied moves — dogfood example') outside the parsed move table, or update test_move_registry_matches_docs_table to scope its regex to the built-in moves table only (e.g. anchor to a known heading).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the complete routing-entry schema for `project.portability` in `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` — including `exec` (one of `1-TURN`/`2-STEP`/`AGENT`/`DET`), `default_posture` (`advisory` or `blocking`), `block_threshold`, and `applies_at.scope` (container and/or leaf).","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states: 'Add one activated project plan-review criterion, `project.portability`, through `.rebar/criteria_routing.json`' — no field values specified.","src/rebar/llm/criteria/overlay.py:151-156: exec_v validated against ('1-TURN', '2-STEP', 'AGENT', 'DET'); src/rebar/llm/criteria/overlay.py:162-167: default_posture validated against ('advisory', 'blocking').","All packaged criteria in src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json supply exec, block_threshold, default_posture, and applies_at explicitly."],"finding":"The plan instructs the implementer to activate `project.portability` via `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` but never specifies the required routing-entry field values (exec tier, default_posture, block_threshold, applies_at.scope). The overlay validator (_validate_routing_entry) enforces a closed enum for exec ('1-TURN' | '2-STEP' | 'AGENT' | 'DET') and default_posture ('advisory' | 'blocking'). Without these values, the entry either fails load-time validation or silently inherits defaults that may be wrong for a Pass-1 LLM criterion.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fddd42728d957b2ec","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section / `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` artifact","norm_id":"n369ba6be5fe8feed","priority":0.066,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Implementer writes the routing entry without exec — entry silently defaults to '1-TURN' (advisory behavior) when the criterion may need '1-TURN' with a specific scope.","Implementer omits applies_at.scope — the criterion runs at both container and leaf, which may be intentional but is nowhere stated in the plan.","Implementer sets default_posture: 'blocking' vs 'advisory' — this gate decision is load-bearing but the plan is silent."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add to the What section or Acceptance Criteria: 'The `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` entry for `project.portability` carries `exec: \"1-TURN\"`, `default_posture: \"advisory\"`, `block_threshold: 0.95`, and `applies_at: {scope: [\"container\", \"leaf\"]}`.' Adjust values to match the intended posture.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify how the four-part finding contract maps to the P1Finding schema fields (e.g. which field carries the 'alternate client shape' and which carries the 'causal mechanism'), or document that the contract is enforced exclusively through the portability prompt text and the positive-fixture tests use real-LLM calls (not FakeRunner) to validate prompt compliance.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'The finder may emit a portability finding only when it supplies all four elements: a citation to the explicit plan detail… a materially different supported client shape… the causal mechanism… a specific, observable breakage scenario.'","src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py:85-106: P1Finding schema fields are finding/criteria/location/evidence/scenarios/impact — no 'client_shape' or 'causal_mechanism' field.","AC: 'Every positive fixture surfaces the four-part finding contract' — tested via pytest, but the test can only check that the FakeRunner emits the right structure, not that the LLM prompt actually enforces it structurally."],"finding":"The four-part finding contract (plan citation + alternate client shape + causal failure mechanism + observable breakage scenario) is stated as prose gate in the plan's 'What' section but is not co-located with any output schema that enforces it. The `P1Finding` Pydantic schema (passes._pass1_model) has fields `finding`, `criteria`, `location`, `evidence`, `scenarios`, `impact` — none map specifically to 'alternate client shape' or 'causal mechanism.' An LLM could emit a finding missing two of the four required elements and it would still pass schema validation. The enforcement mechanism (the portability prompt at `.rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md`) is the only locus of this rule, but neither its structure nor its relationship to these four schema fields is specified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcc3be0329d6ba031","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'The finder may emit a portability finding only when it supplies all four elements'","norm_id":"n49127af30bdd4bb2","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["The portability prompt is written loosely and an LLM emits a finding with only a plan citation and a breakage scenario (two of four), which passes P1Finding schema validation and routes through Pass 2/3 normally.","The test `positive_counterexample_contract` uses a FakeRunner that returns a pre-canned four-part response, so it never actually tests that the prompt enforces the contract."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a fallback clause to Approach step 1: state explicitly that if the offline experiment cannot complete successfully, implementation in step 2 is blocked until the extension-mechanism wiring is verified or the design is revised.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan: 'This de-risks the extension mechanism; it does not become production code.' — no 'if experiment fails, do X' branch.","The operator-attested AC ('A fresh origin/main worktree experiment proves criterion activation…') is tagged [operator-attested] — if attestation cannot be recorded, the plan provides no fallback gate."],"finding":"The offline wiring experiment (Approach step 1) has no stated fallback or resolution protocol if it fails — the plan says 'de-risks the extension mechanism' but is silent on what to do if the experiment cannot be completed successfully, whether implementation should proceed, block, or revise the design.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9e7c8e55b79df027","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Approach and sequencing — Step 1","norm_id":"necc462a81540d087","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The offline experiment reveals that the project fan-in does not work as expected for project.portability — the plan gives no guidance on whether to fix the machinery before proceeding to step 2 or proceed anyway.","The experiment cannot be run (e.g., no clean origin/main worktree available) — the plan provides no alternative evidence path."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add at least one acceptance criterion that validates the portability prompt against a real (non-mocked) LLM call and asserts the four-part contract (citation, alternate shape, causal mechanism, breakage scenario) is present in the output — either as a named live-integration test marker or as an explicit assertion within the operator-attested experiment whose recorded output is checked against the contract.","cohort":["E3","E5","G5"],"criteria":["E5"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["'Every positive fixture surfaces the four-part finding contract: plan citation, alternate client shape, causal failure mechanism, observable breakage scenario. Verify: .venv/bin/python -m pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability.py -k positive_counterexample_contract'","Step 1: 'run an offline experiment' — the word 'offline' and pytest unit-test verify command together imply no live LLM boundary is crossed in the automated gate","ABSENCE: no AC or step explicitly requires validating the portability prompt against a live LLM call and asserting the four-part contract appears in real output"],"finding":"The positive-fixture ACs (`positive_counterexample_contract`) are exercised through pytest unit tests, which strongly implies mocked or offline LLM agents. If so, these tests verify that a pre-canned response satisfies the four-part contract, not that the real portability prompt causes a live LLM to produce the required contract elements. The 'offline experiment' in step 1 exercises plumbing (registry, routing, fan-in, move loader) but may not validate that the real prompt reliably elicits the four-part finding structure from a real LLM. The work can close green while the production prompt is structurally broken or silently emits findings without citation, alternate shape, causal mechanism, or breakage scenario.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f01007ca81508fa44","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — `positive_counterexample_contract` marker; Approach step 1 'offline experiment'; Approach step 3 'focused tests with positive cases'","norm_id":"ndc6e45a32392c907","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The portability prompt is authored without a strict output schema; a real LLM omits the 'causal mechanism' element; pytest passes because the mock returns a pre-structured response; the criterion ships and silently produces incomplete findings in production.","The prompt elicits free-prose findings that contain the right content but not in the structured form the Move renderer expects; unit tests pass; the coaching move fails to render correctly in production."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Extend the operator-attested experiment AC to require that its recorded output include at least one finding demonstrating all four contract elements (quoting each from the actual LLM response), and add a corresponding `live_prompt_contract` pytest marker (even if `@pytest.mark.integration` skipped in CI) that runs the real prompt against a fixture plan and asserts the four parts are present — so the automated gate can be enabled when an LLM key is available.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"7983a75fbd33d8bc","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":204.0,"llm_calls":27,"llm_ms":444706.0,"total_ms":445004.9,"verify_requests":26},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"jira-reb-1003","ticket_type":"epic","verdict":"PASS","verified_at_sha":"b0ac25447203d864463408c933497f21bc1f8dbf"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784162826852250001,"uuid":"0c7392c2-4f2e-43b5-8c7b-f5ee80b67d4d"}